post_text: We’ve got some important athletic updates, Bangor Vikings! According to the most recent executive order from Governor Whitmer, all athletes must wear a mask at all times. This includes during competition. Also, only two spectators per athlete will be admitted to contests, and masks must be worn at all times. Spectators from different households must practice 6 feet of social distance. If you have questions or concerns, please email jmortensen@bangorvikings.org. Go, Vikings!

post_text:
Meal Pickup will be on Sept. 4th from 5-7pm at the HS.

If you are a virtual student, you will receive all your breakfast & lunch for one week.

If you are a hybrid student, you will receive all your breakfast for the week & 3 days of lunches for the days not on site. When you are on campus, lunch will be served.

Breakfast will not be served on site, so you must pick up on Friday, Sept. 4 from 5-7pm at the HS.

Tomorrow is a HALF DAY for our RED GROUP Bangor Vikings. We can’t wait to see you!

South Walnut Elementary School
August 30 at 7:47 PM ·

Good evening South Walnut students and families! We are excited to start another year and look forward to seeing our students in the RED group Monday morning at 7:55 a.m. for a HALF DAY. This is a reminder that only the RED group will be coming to school tomorrow. The WHITE group will attend school on Thursday, September 3rd at 7:55 a.m. The Virtual group will begin working from home on their device on Monday, August 31st, using the Kickstand Platform. It is very important for students in the RED and WHITE group to bring a water bottle, face mask, and their fully-charged device to school each day they attend. If you missed the Technology Device Pick up day, you will need to call the school office at 269-427-6863 x3029 to make an appointment for device pickup. Thank you and have a wonderful night! See you tomorrow, RED GROUP Bangor Vikings!

post_text: Bangor Vikings, JV & Varsity football practices will begin Monday, August 10th, 6-8 PM. Student athletes must each bring their own water bottle, and bottles must not be shared. The attached MHSAA health questionnaire must be filled out prior to participating. It can also be found on the front doors of Bangor High School or on our website. Students who have a physical on file from last school year may participate. Those who do not have a physical on file from last year must have one completed first. For any questions, please email the athletic director at jmortensen@bangorvikings.org.

post_text:
Estimadas familias de la escuela Bangor:

A medida que hacemos planes para el año escolar 2020-21, recibimos continuamente nueva información que puede ser impactante para la forma en que facilitamos el aprendizaje en el otoño. Algunas de las consideraciones más importantes son el nivel de comodidad y las preferencias de nuestras familias escolares. Valoramos su opinión y agradeceríamos sus comentarios y perspectiva con respecto al año escolar 20-21. Tómese un momento para responder al breve Cuestionario de preinscripción de regreso a la escuela incluido con este correo electrónico. También somos conscientes de que las circunstancias en torno al Coronavirus están cambiando activamente y planeamos actualizar a las familias a medida que nos acercamos al inicio del año escolar. Tenga en cuenta que este cuestionario fue diseñado para acompañar el Plan de Regreso a la Escuela 20-21 que estará disponible en el sitio web del distrito en breve. Envíe una respuesta de encuesta por niño. ¡Gracias por tu tiempo!

post_text:
Dear Bangor School Families:

As we make plans for the 2020-21 school year, we are continually receiving new information that may be impactful to how we facilitate learning in the fall. Some of the most important considerations are the comfort level and preferences of our school families. We value your opinion and would appreciate your feedback and perspective regarding the 20-21 school year. Please take a moment to respond to the brief Return to School Pre-Registration Questionnaire included with this email. We are also aware that the circumstances around the Coronavirus are actively changing and plan to update families as we get closer to the start of the school year as well. Please keep in mind, this questionnaire was designed to accompany the 20-21 Back to School Plan that will be available on the district’s website shortly. Please submit one survey response per child. Thank you for your time!

Approximately 200 people from over 11 School Districts have been meeting weekly, along with guidance from the Michigan Department of Education and the Van Buren/Cass health Department to address Stakeholder concerns with the Re-Opening of Schools throughout Michigan.

Equipment return is happening today (6/3) and Bangor Middle School and Bangor High School.

Bangor Middle/High School
June 3 at 7:16 AM ·

Today (6/3) is the day! Bangor Middle & High Schools is hosting a return of school items 10:00-12:00 & 5:00-7:00. Please navigate to the curbside of each main office to drop off textbooks, school owned band instruments, library books, and other school-owned materials you have. At these locations, we will also get any locker items not picked up yet by your request. We will have end-of-year awards and middle school yearbooks, if you purchased one. All Chromebooks will need to be returned to the annex building next to the high school. This is the small white building. Ms. Everett, technology director, will be waiting in the parking lot to assist you. During this process, we will maintain social distancing and attempt to have you remain in your vehicle as we assist you. Thank you for your partnership and cooperation!

I know this has been a crazy spring, and I am just as out-of-sorts as many of you. Anyway, I am thinking of you today, as I think of you often. We will be back on stage next school year, no worries. Excelsior!
Sarge

Continuity of Learning Plan & Remote Education

Bangor Public Schools Continuity of Learning Plan for remote learning has been submitted and approved by the Van Buren Intermediate School District. So what does this mean?

Beginning tomorrow, April 21st, school work will be available for the remainder of the school year. Students in grades Kindergarten through 4th grade, who attend South Walnut Elementary, will be able to pick up paper packets between the hours of 8:00 am and 3:00 pm.

Students in grades 5th through 12th, your work has been uploaded to your google classroom account. Please make sure you are logging in to your school email daily to access your work.

Also, please encourage your Middle School and High School students to check their school email daily if possible.

post_text:
Attention Current & Future Apple Tree Preschool families:

For our current families, we have boxes of supplies and materials including paint, scissors, glue sticks, colored pencils, playing cards, wooden alphabet magnetic letters, dry erase foam blocks, and more! Email Mrs. Shafer at kshafer@bangorvikings.org or Miss Shafer at bshafer@bangorvikings.org to arrange collection of materials.

For our future families, if your child turns 4 on or before December 1st, it's time to start your application! Get started with this online application, and we'll collect any documents we need at a later point. Email Mrs. Shafer at kshafer@bangorvikings.org with questions.

Earlier today, Governor Whitmer placed an Executive Order of "Stay Home, Stay Safe." This has brought about questions concerning the Food Service Programs the Bangor Public Schools has been doing to feed our children. I have included a copy of the correction from Governor Whitmer. We will continue with our Food Delivery Program, as this is considered essential workforce.

Last week, Wednesday, the District provided bags of food for 673 children (2 breakfasts, 2 lunches, each totaling 2692 meals). Friday meal bags were provided for 904 children (3 breakfasts and 3 lunches for a total of 5424 meals). Over a 2 day period, Bangor Public Schools provided children with 8116 meals. We will continue providing as long as the State of Michigan allows.

Thank you to all who have helped make this possible for our children!

Lynn Johnson, Superintendent
Bangor Public Schools

Monday morning, the administration team from the school will be meeting to complete plans to help provide the following supports:

*Family Resource Packets so that your children can continue their Educational Progress

*Plans to provide free meals for all those students in need

Bangor Public Schools wants to thank you for your continued patience and understanding as we continue to monitor this…

post_text:
Dear Bangor Vikings Families,

Governor Whitmer and State Superintendent Michael Rice have closed all schools in the State of Michigan beginning Monday, March 16th, 2020 through Monday, April 6th, 2020. The Administration at Bangor Public Schools is working on a plan to help all students and families within our school district to work through this unfortunate situation. Please be patient over the next couple of days as we work through options to provide the best possible alternatives for your children's health and safety during these trying times.

Patients with confirmed infection have reportedly had mild to severe respiratory illness with symptoms of:

-Fever
-Cough
-Shortness of breath

shared_text:
Meyers Biology
>>>>>>> master
March 7 at 11:10 AM ·

Haven’t posted in here in a long time. Here are some photos of spring in Bangor: Room 12. We have Botany and Wilderness Survival in full swing. We found skunk cabbage coming up on March 5 and we are trying friction fires with a bow drill in wilderness survival. Its not easy. We also tapped several sugar maples and we collected about 20 liters of sap. We are boiling it down on hot plates. It takes a long time. The students are learning a ton. In Biology we are discussing modern genetics, dna, crspr, and of course the current pandemic. Been warning about this for years, look out, here it comes.

Back in November, 2019, high school senior, and member of the Valhalla Vikings ESports club, Eric, and I were asked to present about high school ESports at WMU. Coach Ward and I took our three senior gamers on a field trip there and had a great time!

The powers that be were so impressed with Eric, that the Executive Director of MACUL requested that Eric and I present during the MACUL ESports conference on Saturday, March 14th. I am very excited about this, and I hope good things come out of it for Eric. He is an excellent gamer, and I think he could go far in the ESports industry. Congrats Eric.

Bangor Vikings Band Program
March 5 at 7:46 PM ·

Today was an extraordinary day for both our 7/8 Grade Concert Band and HS Concert Band. Both groups represented our school and community well in every way.

I am pleased to announce that both groups earned a Division 1 at MSBOA District 6 Band Festival. This is the highest rating and both groups are now qualified for festival.

It was also nice to have such amazing support from administration, family and friends who were able to make it out to the performance. Thank you to all who attended including those who helped chaperone.

link:
Good Afternoon Bangor Families,

We would like to inform you of upcoming events that will take place this week.
On Monday, February 17th, there will be a Black History Month program in the High School Auditorium at 5:30 pm. Dinner will immediately follow the program and this is open to the community. Dinner will be provided by Gary's Catering of Bangor.

On Wednesday, February 19th, the Bangor Bands will have a Pizza night at Silver Beach Pizza. As long as you have the flyer, they will donate 20% back to the Band program. For a copy of the flyer, please stop by the middle or high school offices.

Thursday and Friday will be 1/2 day's of school. Thursday will be Parent Teacher Conferences from 1:00-4:00 and 5:00-8:00. During this time the middle school book fair will be open to families in the library. We hope you are able to join us!

On Sunday, February 23rd, there will be a pre-festival Band concert at 2:00 pm in the high school gymnasium.

Please mark your calendars. Thank you and Go Vikings!

column17: Tomorrow is Winterfest! Wear your red & white gear to show your Viking school spirit! Come support our Varsity basketball teams, who will be sporting throwback uniforms, at 6:00 PM & 7:30 PM. The Winterfest court will be announced during halftime of the boys game, and the semi-formal dance will follow the games and go until 11:30 PM. Happy Winterfest, Bangor Vikings!

post_text:
Bangor Middle/High School
February 11 at 8:25 PM ·

Good evening, Bangor Middle School families! In celebration of Winterfest, we will have a middle school dance Thursday, February 13th, immediately following school until 4:30 PM. Tickets are available at lunch for $2 in advance or $3 at the door. Only currently enrolled students in grades 5-8 are allowed to attend. Please make sure all students have transportation following the event.

Good evening! On Monday, February 17th 2020, Bangor Public Schools will be hosting a community wide Black History Month Celebration. The program will begin at 5:30 PM in the High School Auditorium. The program will include music, a guest speaker, poster contest for grades K-12, and other activities. Following the program, there will be a dinner provided by Gary's Catering in the High School cafeteria. All community members are invited to attend. Hope to see you there!
